– The mayor of an eastern Arkansas city has a pointed message for residents who he says aren’t following social distancing guidelines to curb the coronavirus.
“With all emotion and no disrespect, stay your ass at home,” West Memphis Mayor Marco McClendon said in a video posted on the city’s Facebook page Tuesday.
West Memphis Mayor Marco McClendon (Photo: Smith Artisan, AP)The West Memphis mayor told The Associated Press on Wednesday that his message was spurred by a rise in cases in his city and frustration over some younger residents not taking the threat seriously.
Crittenden County, where West Memphis is located, has the second highest number of cases among Arkansas’ 75 counties, with 121.
Arkansas’ governor has shut down public schools for the rest of the academic year, closed many businesses and banned gatherings of more than 10 people.